 Sure, I can help you with that. Here's an example XML file for your mission plan:
```php
<mission>
    <starting_point>
        <x>0</x>
        <y>0</y>
    </starting_point>
    <tasks>
        <task id="1">
            <name>Measure cos.</name>
            <destination>
                <x>4</x>
                <y>4</y>
            </destination>
        </task>
        <task id="2">
            <name>Take pictures of nearby trees.</name>
            <destination>
                <x>6</x>
                <y>6</y>
            </destination>
        </task>
        <task id="3">
            <name>Measure another tree as far away as possible for co2.</name>
            <destination>
                <x>10</x>
                <y>10</y>
            </destination>
        </task>
        <task id="4">
            <name>Take pictures of nearby trees.</name>
            <destination>
                <x>8</x>
                <y>8</y>
            </destination>
        </task>
        <task id="5">
            <name>Take a temperature reading at any one of the northern most trees.</name>
            <destination>
                <x>12</x>
                <y>12</y>
            </destination>
        </task>
        <task id="6">
            <name>Return to end.</name>
            <destination>
                <x>0</x>
                <y>0</y>
            </destination>
        </task>
    </tasks>
</mission>
```
In this example, the starting point is at (0,0). The tasks are numbered from 1 to 6 and each task has a name and a destination. The destinations for each task are represented by their x and y coordinates in the orchard.

You can adjust the coordinates of the destinations as needed to match your specific mission plan. Let me know if you have any questions or need further assistance. 